userPromptTemplate:
A new capability needs to be added to this existing system.

## New capability requested:
{{CAPABILITY_DESCRIPTION}}

## What already exists (from capability inventory):
{{CAPABILITY_INVENTORY_JSON}}

## Project conventions (IRON_RULE only):
{{IRON_RULE_CONVENTIONS}}

For the requested capability, produce a JSON analysis:
```
{
  "forCapability": "<capability name>",
  "reuse": [
    {
      "service": "<existing class name>",
      "for": "<what aspect of the new capability it covers>",
      "how": "<which specific methods to call, what parameters>",
      "confidence": <0.0-1.0>,
      "why": "<reasoning: why this service covers this need>"
    }
  ],
  "extend": [
    {
      "service": "<existing class name>",
      "change": "<what to add to the existing class>",
      "pattern": "<existing pattern in the class to follow for the extension>",
      "why": "<reasoning: why extension rather than reuse or create>"
    }
  ],
  "create": [
    {
      "name": "<new class name>",
      "reason": "<why no existing class covers this>",
      "nearestPattern": "<existing class whose structure is most similar>",
      "keyMethods": ["<method signature 1>", "<method signature 2>"]
    }
  ]
}
```

Reasoning rules:
- REUSE requires: the existing class was designed for this type of data/operation, AND it exposes the methods needed
- EXTEND requires: the existing class is structurally correct but missing a specific feature this capability needs
- CREATE requires: no existing class covers this, OR adapting an existing class would violate its original design
- When confidence < 0.70 for a REUSE decision, use CREATE instead
- Always name the nearestPattern for CREATE items — even if nothing is close, name what is least different

Output ONLY the JSON object. No explanation.
